---
description: "Use Pathname for file/directory paths (coerce in constructors), / operator for joins instead of File.join, _FILE suffix on path constants."
alwaysApply: false
---

# Strong types for paths

Use `Pathname` for file/directory paths, not `String`. Coerce in constructors
with `Pathname()`.

```ruby
# BAD
def initialize(dir:)
  @dir = dir  # could be String or Pathname
end

# GOOD
def initialize(dir:)
  @dir = Pathname(dir)
end
```

Use Pathname's `/` operator for path joins instead of `File.join`:

```ruby
# BAD
path = File.join(@dir.to_s, "deps.lock")

# GOOD
path = @dir / "deps.lock"
```

Constants holding filenames get a `_FILE` suffix:

```ruby
# BAD
DEPS_LOCK = "deps.lock"
DEPS_CMAKE = "deps.cmake"

# GOOD
DEPS_LOCK_FILE = "deps.lock"
DEPS_CMAKE_FILE = "deps.cmake"
```
